# Code owners for meta-workspace.
#
# Syntax: <path pattern>  <owner(s)>. The LAST matching pattern wins, so the
# more specific, sensitive paths are listed after the catch-all.
#
# Ownership is documented here now. Enforcement is intentionally OFF in the
# branch ruleset (`require_code_owner_review: false`) because a single
# maintainer cannot review their own pull requests. Flip the ruleset's
# `require_code_owner_review` to true once a second reviewer exists — at which
# point these path rules will require owner sign-off on the sensitive areas
# below without forcing review on routine changes.

# Default owner for the whole repository.
*                                   @shingonoide

# Supply-chain- and CI-sensitive surfaces.
/.github/                           @shingonoide
/deny.toml                          @shingonoide
/Cargo.toml                         @shingonoide
/Cargo.lock                         @shingonoide

# Security-sensitive: the cross-harness policy enforcement engine and the
# security policy itself warrant extra scrutiny once review is enforced.
/tooling/src/commands/policy.rs     @shingonoide
/SECURITY.md                        @shingonoide
